## USER RESEARCH

**Top 5 Pain Points** *(sourced: Quora, WeddingWire forums, SalonGeek, beauty community discussions)*

1. **"I don't know which one to ask for and I'm embarrassed to admit it at the salon"** — first-timers freeze at the question and default to whichever the tech recommends, with no idea if it suits their lifestyle or nail health.
2. **"My last set lifted/broke and I don't know if it was the product or the tech"** — users can't diagnose whether their set failed due to product choice, skill, or aftercare; they don't know what question to even ask next time.
3. **"I'm worried about damaging my natural nails underneath"** — nail health anxiety is the #1 emotional brake on the decision; people delay booking because they fear long-term damage.
4. **"I need them to last for my wedding/event but I don't know which holds up better"** — high-stakes occasion makes the decision feel higher-risk; they want a clear recommendation not generic advice.
5. **"Gel looks more natural but I've heard acrylic is stronger — which do I actually need for almond shape specifically?"** — they've absorbed conflicting information from the internet and want someone to just tell them which one wins for the almond shape.

**User Sentiment:** Anxious but motivated — they've committed to getting almond nails but feel underprepared to make the product decision confidently.

